  "narrative_arc": "Carpenter who had a heart attack and can't work but is deemed \"fit for work\" by a computer assessment. Loach documents every step of the UK benefits system — the online-only application he can't navigate, the Jobcentre sanctions, the food bank, the appeal tribunal. He dies of a heart attack in the waiting room of the appeals office.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Daniel Blake is the most detailed fictional map of benefits system navigation ever filmed. Layer 2 (Systems) is documented with such precision that the film was used as evidence in UK parliamentary hearings on welfare reform. His dome maps the bureaucratic kill zone.",
